        <p> So we only looked around in the shop, which didn't gave much. As we should find out later, it was recently renovated and might have been worth another look at the dining room.
            Since we still had no explicit plan for the day, we decided to go to the Hard Rock Hotel on the small island of Santosa.
            Maybe that's better and besides some other interesting -sounding attractions, there is also a beach there. So said. </p>
        <p> You come to Santosa in 4 species. By bus, ship, the monorail or cable car.
            We chose the Monorail because it brought us directly to the beach. On the way there we learned that Santosa is almost the attraction island.
            There is not only beach and a hard rock hotel, but also a universal studios adventure park, an aquarium and even indoor skydiving is possible there. </p>
        <p> There were not long on the beach, because it was quite small and it was just too warm to fry in the sun.
            So after a cold drink we continued through the heat to the Hard Rock Hotel.
            The hotel was really nice and the service was much friendlier.
            There we even found some nice shirts for ourselves. </p>
