        <p> Next we wanted to try some more attraction on the island.
            Unfortunately, the aquarium was too full for us and unfortunately it was too late for Universal Studios.
            We then decided that we slowly make our way to the garden by the Bay. </p>
        <p> It is a kind of modern botanical garden, in the center of which there are several high artificial trees that are slowly overgrown by foliage.
            There is a light and music show every evening. Star Wars is currently on the program.
            We had already seen this yesterday from the viewing platform of the Marina Bay Sands Hotel. </p>
        <p> When we arrived there, as expected, we moved a large number of people towards the artificial trees.
            We simply followed the mass and with every meter there were more people.
            After the show was apparently delayed and then didn't even start music with Star Wars, it clicked with us.
            There is something special here today.
            We urged ourselves through the crowds to see better and got the information that was a birthday party for the gardens.
            Despite that we were only 50 m away from the trees, we could see almost nothing of the show. </p>
